# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# herocast-web — secrets template (forkability bar, hero-org/herocast#754)
#
# LOCAL DEV:  copy this file to `.dev.vars` (gitignored) and fill in real values.
#             `wrangler dev` / `vite dev` load `.dev.vars` automatically.
#
# PRODUCTION: `.dev.vars` is dev-only. Push each secret to the deployed Worker:
#               wrangler secret put NEYNAR_API_KEY
#               wrangler secret put SUPABASE_URL
#               wrangler secret put SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
#             On the edge these are read via `import { env } from 'cloudflare:workers'`
#             (see src/lib/env.ts) — NOT from .dev.vars.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Neynar (Farcaster API). Server-side only.
NEYNAR_API_KEY=your-neynar-api-key

# Supabase. Server-side client (auth cookie read + login callback write).
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key

# NOTE: this file is WORKER-RUNTIME config only (read via cloudflare:workers /
# process.env). It does NOT feed Vite's import.meta.env. The browser Supabase client
# (Phase 2) reads VITE_*-prefixed vars, which Vite inlines at BUILD time from .env.local
# (local) or the build environment (prod) — see .env.local.example. Server secrets here
# are runtime; VITE_* are build-time. Don't mix them up.
